# PART 2 · The Component Tree

This is the single most important diagram in this entire guide. **Print it. Stick it next to your monitor. Reference it constantly.**

```
App                                    ← The root. Holds all state. The CEO.
│
├── Navbar                             ← Top bar across the full width
│   ├── BrandLogo                      ← "SkyCast" text + hamburger menu icon
│   ├── LocationDisplay                ← "📍 Khulna, Bangladesh"
│   ├── SearchBar                      ← Text input + GPS detect button
│   ├── ThemeToggle                    ← "Light" / "Dark" button
│   └── UserProfile                    ← Bell icon, settings icon, avatar, "Wow Rakibul"
│
└── MainLayout                         ← Two-column CSS Grid container
    │
    ├── LeftColumn                     ← Everything on the left side
    │   │
    │   ├── CurrentWeatherHero         ← Big card at top
    │   │   (time, temp, icon, "Rainy", "Feels Like 35°",
    │   │    description text, Fahrenheit/Celsius dropdown)
    │   │
    │   ├── StatsGrid                  ← 3×2 grid of small cards
    │   │   ├── StatCard               ← Air Quality: 156
    │   │   ├── StatCard               ← Wind: 1 mph
    │   │   ├── StatCard               ← Humidity: 54%
    │   │   ├── StatCard               ← Visibility: 3 mi
    │   │   ├── StatCard               ← Pressure: 27.65 in
    │   │   └── StatCard               ← Temperature: 66°
    │   │
    │   └── SunMoonCard                ← Bottom section with arcs
    │       ├── AstroRow               ← ☀️ Sunrise 5:43AM ... arc ... Sunset 5:43AM
    │       └── AstroRow               ← 🌙 Moonrise 5:43AM ... arc ... Moonset 5:43AM
    │
    └── RightColumn                    ← Everything on the right side
        │
        ├── ForecastHeader             ← Top strip of the right panel
        │   ├── TabGroup               ← [Today] [Tomorrow] [10 Days]
        │   └── MonthlyCastButton      ← "See Monthly Cast" red button
        │
        └── ForecastList               ← Scrollable list of rows
            ├── ForecastRow            ← 1AM | ⛅ Mostly Cloudy | 12°C | Wind: 120km | Humidity: 59%
            ├── ForecastRow            ← 2AM | ...
            ├── ForecastRow            ← 3AM | ...
            ├── ForecastRow            ← 4AM | ...
            ├── ForecastRow            ← 5AM | ...
            ├── ForecastRow            ← 6AM | ...
            └── ForecastRow            ← 7AM | ...
```

### The Numbers

| Metric | Count |
|---|---|
| Total component instances on screen | ~26 |
| Unique components you actually build | **~14** |
| Components that are just "display boxes" | 10+ |
| Components with any interactive logic | Only 3-4 |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **The key realization:** You see ~26 things on screen but you only write ~14 component files. `StatCard` alone eliminates 5 files worth of repetition. `ForecastRow` eliminates 6 more. React's component model saves you enormous amounts of work.

