# PART 15 · The Pre-Build Checklist

Before writing EACH component, answer these 5 questions on paper or in your head:

## ✍️ The 5 Questions

### Q1: What does this component display?
Write one sentence. Example: "StatCard displays an icon, a label, and a value inside a rounded box."

### Q2: What props does it need?
List each prop by name and type. Example: "icon (string), label (string), value (string)."

### Q3: Does it have any children components?
If yes, which ones? Example: "StatsGrid has 6 StatCard children."

### Q4: Does it need any state?
If yes, what and why? Example: "TabGroup needs activeTab state because the user can change which tab is selected."

### Q5: What CSS layout does it use?
Flexbox or Grid? Horizontal or vertical? Example: "StatCard uses Flexbox, vertical direction, centered content."

## Worked Examples

### Example: StatCard

| Question | Answer |
|---|---|
| Q1: Displays? | An icon, a label ("Wind"), and a value ("1 mph") in a small rounded card |
| Q2: Props? | `icon` (string), `label` (string), `value` (string) |
| Q3: Children? | No children components. Just HTML elements inside it. |
| Q4: State? | No. It just displays what it receives. |
| Q5: CSS? | Flexbox column. Icon on top-left, label below, value at bottom in large text. Rounded corners, subtle border. |

### Example: RightColumn

| Question | Answer |
|---|---|
| Q1: Displays? | The entire right side panel: tabs at the top, forecast rows below |
| Q2: Props? | `forecastData` (object with today/tomorrow/tenDays arrays) |
| Q3: Children? | `ForecastHeader` (which has `TabGroup`) and `ForecastList` (which has `ForecastRow`s) |
| Q4: State? | Yes — `activeTab` to track which tab (Today/Tomorrow/10 Days) is selected |
| Q5: CSS? | Flexbox column. Header at top, scrollable list filling remaining space. |

