# PART 16 · What to Google When You're Stuck

When you're stuck, what you search for matters. Here are the exact queries for the most common problems you'll face:

### Layout Problems

| Problem | Search This |
|---|---|
| Can't get two columns side-by-side | "CSS Grid two column layout" |
| Cards are stretching weird in a grid | "CSS Grid equal height cards" |
| Content is overflowing the right panel | "CSS overflow y scroll container" |
| Navbar items won't space out properly | "Flexbox space between align center" |
| The page isn't centered | "CSS center content max-width margin auto" |

### React Problems

| Problem | Search This |
|---|---|
| Component isn't showing up | "React component not rendering check" |
| Props showing as `undefined` | "React props undefined debugging" |
| List is rendering but without unique identifiers | "React key prop when rendering list" |
| Don't know how to pass a function to child | "React pass function as prop to child component" |
| Parent needs to know about child event | "React child to parent communication callback" |
| State change not reflecting | "React useState not updating immediately" |

### CSS Problems

| Problem | Search This |
|---|---|
| CSS in one component leaking to another | "React CSS modules vs BEM naming" |
| Background gradient not covering full page | "CSS background gradient full page body min-height" |
| Rounded corners with inner shadow like the design | "CSS border-radius box-shadow card design" |
| Making a single card match the design exactly | "CSS card design with icon and text layout" |

### When You're Completely Lost

| Situation | Do This |
|---|---|
| "I don't know where to start" | Re-read Phase 1 of Part 12. Build one `StatCard` with hardcoded props. |
| "My layout is broken and I can't figure out why" | Open browser DevTools → Inspect → check the box model of each element |
| "I've been stuck for 30+ minutes" | Take a 10-minute break. Then try deleting your failed attempt and starting that ONE component over |
| "The design is too complex" | Build the simplified version first (just `SearchBar`, `CurrentWeatherHero`, 3 `StatCard`s, 3 `ForecastRow`s). Add the advanced layout later. |

---

# THE BIG PICTURE — Two Analogies to Remember

## 🍽️ Analogy 1: The Restaurant

| SkyCast Component | Restaurant Role | What They Do |
|---|---|---|
| `App` | Restaurant Owner | Knows everything. Holds all the data. Makes all the big decisions. |
| `MainLayout` | Floor Plan | Decides there's a dining room (left) and a bar (right). Doesn't serve food. |
| `StatsGrid` | Waiter | Takes data from the kitchen (App) and delivers it to the right tables (StatCards). |
| `StatCard` | Plate | Doesn't cook. Doesn't take orders. Just presents whatever food (data) is placed on it, beautifully. |
| `SearchBar` | Front Desk Phone | When a customer calls (user types), the phone doesn't decide what to do — it rings the owner (calls the callback), and the owner handles it. |
| `ForecastRow` | Menu Item Card | One row on the menu board. It doesn't decide the menu — the kitchen tells it what to display. |

## 🏗️ Analogy 2: Building a House

| Phase | House Building | SkyCast Building |
|---|---|---|
| Phase 1 | Make individual bricks | Build `StatCard`, `ForecastRow` |
| Phase 2 | Assemble bricks into walls | Build `StatsGrid`, `ForecastList` |
| Phase 3 | Put up the frame and roof | Build `MainLayout`, `Navbar` |
| Phase 4 | Install plumbing and electricity | Add state and interactivity |
| Phase 5 | Connect to city water supply | Connect to weather API |
| Phase 6 | Paint, decorate, furnish | Polish colors, animations, responsive design |

You wouldn't connect a house to the city water supply before building the walls. Same with SkyCast — don't touch the API until the UI is complete.

